-- allium: 3
-- specs/cuda-native-dispatch/libmgpu_subgraph_capture.allium
--
-- Status: PLACEHOLDER. Bound by PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md
-- commit C7 (libmgpu port to captured subgraphs).
--
-- Scope: libmgpu's per-device subgraphs (built by the Phase 46
-- mgpu split builders, ~ik_llama.cpp/mgpu/) capture cleanly into
-- the outer multi-device cudaGraph_t established by C4. The CLIP
-- encoder's tensor-parallel matmul + cross-device REDUCE chain
-- produces byte-identical output to the pre-phase non-captured
-- libmgpu evaluation. The Phase 46 closure baseline sha
-- fb5167dbc1e7f95b is the binding reference output for all 10
-- vision-encode samples.
--
-- Why this spec exists: libmgpu is the PRIMARY consumer of the
-- new dispatch (PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md §1.2). Phase 46 made
-- the openmp-parallel libmgpu path deterministic via three default-
-- on patches; C7 deletes the openmp dispatch from libmgpu and the
-- per-device subgraphs become captured subgraphs in the outer
-- multi-device graph. This spec binds equivalence between
-- pre-phase libmgpu output (Phase 46 closure baseline) and the
-- post-phase captured-graph output.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entity for libmgpu split builder
--     (MgpuSplitBuilder, MgpuPerDeviceSubgraph).
--   - Contract SubgraphCapturesCleanly — each per-device subgraph,
--     when called from inside cudaStreamCaptureModeRelaxed on the
--     outer stream, emits its nodes into the outer graph without
--     introducing a nested BeginCapture/EndCapture pair (C3 in-
--     capture awareness).
--   - Contract OutputBitIdenticalToPhase46 — running the captured
--     graph on the Phase 46 production CLIP vision request produces
--     reasoning_content sha256 = fb5167dbc1e7f95b for all 10
--     LATENCY_N samples.
--   - Contract OpenmpDispatchAbsent — libmgpu's eval path no
--     longer contains #pragma omp parallel or std::barrier calls.
--
-- CODE REFS:
--   ik_llama.cpp/mgpu/*.{cpp,cu}                 mgpu split builders
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/mtmd/                  CLIP encoder integration
--   PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md §1.2          libmgpu motivation
--   project_phase46_b5e_closed (auto-memory)    Phase 46 closure baseline
--
-- TBD: fill content when C7 lands. The CLIP equivalence test
-- (test-libmgpu-subgraph-capture.cpp) is the binding mechanism.

allium 3

